

# dooapps releases repo: track only release artifacts and minimal metadata
# Strategy: ignore everything by default, then whitelist what we explicitly want.

# 1) Ignore everything
*

# 2) Allow directory traversal so whitelisted files inside subfolders are kept
!*/

# 3) Always keep the repo control files and docs
!.gitignore
!LICENSE
!*.md
!*.txt
!CHANGELOG.md
!SECURITY.md
!KEYS.md
!README.md

# 4) CocoaPods: keep podspecs
!*.podspec

# 5) Release artifacts (archives/binaries)
!*.zip
!*.tar
!*.tar.gz
!*.tgz
!*.aar

# Optional: allow vendored XCFrameworks (if you choose zero-network installs)
!*.xcframework
!*.xcframework/**

# 6) Checksums and signatures
!*.sha256
!*.sha512
!SHA256SUMS
!SHA512SUMS
!*.sig
!*.asc

# 7) Optional manifests / metadata (keep if you publish release indices)
!*.json
!*.yml
!*.yamldocs/
